## Component structure
- Place each component in its own folder: `src/components/<Name>/`.
- The main file is `src/components/<Name>/<Name>.tsx`.
- Locales live alongside the component in `src/components/<Name>/locales/` with `en.json` and `ja.json` at minimum.

## Props & typing
- Define props as an interface named `I<Name>Props`.
- Include `className?: string` in props for style extension.
- Avoid `any`; keep strict null checks and explicit boolean checks.

## i18n
- Import `@/i18n.ts` at the top of components using translations.
- Use `useTranslation(["common", "<namespace>"])`.
- Provide `defaultValue` fallbacks in `t()` where helpful.

## Styling & class names
- Use Tailwind utility classes.
- Use `clsx` for className composition; avoid custom helpers.
- Inputs: apply focus styles (e.g., `focus:border-blue-500 focus:ring-blue-500`).
- Buttons: primary actions use `bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 focus:ring-blue-500`.

## Imports & files
- Use alias imports `@/*` for anything under `src`.
- Include `.ts`/`.tsx` extensions in imports per ESLint config.
- Client components must start with `'use client';`.
- No prop spreading; pass explicit props.

## Accessibility
- Provide labels and/or `aria-label` for interactive elements and inputs.

## Example
```
src/components/Example/Example.tsx
src/components/Example/locales/en.json
src/components/Example/locales/ja.json
```

```tsx
'use client';

import React from 'react';
import type { JSX } from 'react';
import clsx from 'clsx';
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';
import '@/i18n.ts';

export interface IExampleProps {
  className?: string;
}

export default function Example({ className }: IExampleProps): JSX.Element {
  const { t } = useTranslation(['common', 'example']);
  return (
    <section className={clsx('bg-white rounded-lg p-6', className)}>
      <h2 className="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">{t('title')}</h2>
    </section>
  );
}
